Text.LocalizedString: Do you like being a farmer? Is it fun?//I bet it’s a lot of fun.

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad say it’s hard work too.//You have to work hard on your farm, and I have to work hard at school!
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad say it’s hard work too.//You have to work hard on your farm, and I have to work hard at school!

Text.SourceString: All the kids in my class are really nice.
Text.LocalizedString: All the kids in my class are really nice.

Text.SourceString: One day, I wanna explore the cavern. Mom and Dad say I’m not old enough yet, but I’ll be an adult soon, so I can do it then.
Text.LocalizedString: One day, I wanna explore the cavern. Mom and Dad say I’m not old enough yet, but I’ll be an adult soon, so I can do it then.

Text.SourceString: I’m basically already an adult.//I can take care of myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m basically already an adult.//I can take care of myself.

Text.SourceString: See that tree out there? I think Dad said it’s called a birch tree.//Lots of birds like to nest there.
Text.LocalizedString: See that tree out there? I think Dad said it’s called a birch tree.//Lots of birds like to nest there.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> got this really cool new video game for his birthday. It lets you pretend to be a farmer.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> got this really cool new video game for his birthday. It lets you pretend to be a farmer.

Text.SourceString: I guess you don’t have to play that, huh?//You can just go be a farmer on your farm!
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you don’t have to play that, huh?//You can just go be a farmer on your farm!

Text.SourceString: I’m reading this cool book series about cats living in the forest.//They form clans and hunt for food and everything.//<portrait=surprised>How cool is that?!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m reading this cool book series about cats living in the forest.//They form clans and hunt for food and everything.//<portrait=surprised>How cool is that?!

Text.SourceString: Have you ever seen the wildlife movie called <Italic>Prince of Paws</>?//<portrait=happy>Mom and Dad made that!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever seen the wildlife movie called <Italic>Prince of Paws</>?//<portrait=happy>Mom and Dad made that!

Text.SourceString: It’s all about lions in the savanna.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s all about lions in the savanna.

Text.SourceString: People get really freaked out when I tell them I’ve touched a crocodile, but I really did it once!//In a big swamp!
Text.LocalizedString: People get really freaked out when I tell them I’ve touched a crocodile, but I really did it once!//In a big swamp!

Text.SourceString: It was scary and fun at the same time!
Text.LocalizedString: It was scary and fun at the same time!

Text.SourceString: You should go to the library sometime. They have books for literally everything there!
Text.LocalizedString: You should go to the library sometime. They have books for literally everything there!

Text.SourceString: I even found one about blue jays.
Text.LocalizedString: I even found one about blue jays.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I can help <NPCName>Archie</> at his vet office when we’re both grown-ups.//I want to help animals any way I can.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I can help <NPCName>Archie</> at his vet office when we’re both grown-ups.//I want to help animals any way I can.

Text.SourceString: I’d get really sad if a sick bird came in, though.
Text.LocalizedString: I’d get really sad if a sick bird came in, though.

Text.SourceString: Do you think there’s any animals out there we haven’t discovered yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think there’s any animals out there we haven’t discovered yet?

Text.SourceString: What if I discovered a new bird? I’d be super famous!
Text.LocalizedString: What if I discovered a new bird? I’d be super famous!

Text.SourceString: I wish I could draw better. Sometimes I try to draw the birds I see, but they end up looking like sticks.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could draw better. Sometimes I try to draw the birds I see, but they end up looking like sticks.

Text.SourceString: It’s okay. The dogs <NPCName>Archie</> draws look like brooms.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s okay. The dogs <NPCName>Archie</> draws look like brooms.

Text.SourceString: I built lots of snowmen and got lots of toys from the Winter market last season.
Text.LocalizedString: I built lots of snowmen and got lots of toys from the Winter market last season.

Text.SourceString: I hope this year’s Winter is as fun as last year’s!
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this year’s Winter is as fun as last year’s!

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad told me in the Spring, a bunch of animals come out of hibernation.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad told me in the Spring, a bunch of animals come out of hibernation.

Text.SourceString: They stop sleeping and come out for food.//Everything’s waking up for Spring!
Text.LocalizedString: They stop sleeping and come out for food.//Everything’s waking up for Spring!

Text.SourceString: A bumblebee got stuck in my room yesterday. It almost stung me too!
Text.LocalizedString: A bumblebee got stuck in my room yesterday. It almost stung me too!

Text.SourceString: That wouldn’t have happened if it was still Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: That wouldn’t have happened if it was still Winter.

Text.SourceString: I don’t wanna do my reading. It’s too hot out here to do anything.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t wanna do my reading. It’s too hot out here to do anything.

Text.SourceString: Why is it so hot? It keeps getting hotter every day.
Text.LocalizedString: Why is it so hot? It keeps getting hotter every day.

Text.SourceString: How many days until Winter starts?
Text.LocalizedString: How many days until Winter starts?

Text.SourceString: I wonder if <NPCName>Archie</> wants to go swimming today.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if <NPCName>Archie</> wants to go swimming today.

Text.SourceString: I found a spider in my room yesterday, but I let him stay there.//Fall is supposed to be a spooky time of year, anyway!
Text.LocalizedString: I found a spider in my room yesterday, but I let him stay there.//Fall is supposed to be a spooky time of year, anyway!

Text.SourceString: Plus he eats bugs and stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: Plus he eats bugs and stuff.

Text.SourceString: The crunchy leaves outside are so much fun to jump in!//Me and <NPCName>Archie</> and <NPCName>Taco</> take turns making piles and jumping in them.
Text.LocalizedString: The crunchy leaves outside are so much fun to jump in!//Me and <NPCName>Archie</> and <NPCName>Taco</> take turns making piles and jumping in them.

Text.SourceString: I wanna get a new book to read.//What should I get?
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna get a new book to read.//What should I get?

Text.SourceString: How about something spooky with animals?//That sounds like fun.
Text.LocalizedString: How about something spooky with animals?//That sounds like fun.

Text.SourceString: <Italic>Woo-hoo!</> Bring on the snow and cold! Happy Winter!
Text.LocalizedString: <Italic>Woo-hoo!</> Bring on the snow and cold! Happy Winter!

Text.SourceString: There’s so many fun things that happen in Winter.//You get to build snowmen, visit the Winter market, curl up inside with a big blankie…
Text.LocalizedString: There’s so many fun things that happen in Winter.//You get to build snowmen, visit the Winter market, curl up inside with a big blankie…

Text.SourceString: I mean, a big blanket. Blankies are what little kids have.
Text.LocalizedString: I mean, a big blanket. Blankies are what little kids have.

Text.SourceString: I wish it were always this cold. Maybe I should move to somewhere colder when I grow up.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish it were always this cold. Maybe I should move to somewhere colder when I grow up.

Text.SourceString: I hear Pokyo gets really cold in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: I hear Pokyo gets really cold in Winter.

Text.SourceString: I keep getting– Ah!
Text.LocalizedString: I keep getting– Ah!

Text.SourceString: I keep getting rain in my eyes.
Text.LocalizedString: I keep getting rain in my eyes.

Text.SourceString: Where’s Mom and Dad? I wanna go home. It’s too wet out here.
Text.LocalizedString: Where’s Mom and Dad? I wanna go home. It’s too wet out here.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I’m in here. I don’t wanna get all wet in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I’m in here. I don’t wanna get all wet in the rain.

Text.SourceString: Are there any cartoons on TV? I can’t play outside if it’s raining like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Are there any cartoons on TV? I can’t play outside if it’s raining like this.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> said he was gonna visit <NPCName>Taco</> today.//I wonder if he went in the rain.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> said he was gonna visit <NPCName>Taco</> today.//I wonder if he went in the rain.

Text.SourceString: Are the birds gonna be okay in the wind?//It’s blowing so hard!
Text.LocalizedString: Are the birds gonna be okay in the wind?//It’s blowing so hard!

Text.SourceString: The ocean looks so angry!//I don’t wanna go swimming right now.
Text.LocalizedString: The ocean looks so angry!//I don’t wanna go swimming right now.

Text.SourceString: Can you see anything in this storm?
Text.LocalizedString: Can you see anything in this storm?

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess there’s lightning, but I wish the sun was out like normal.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess there’s lightning, but I wish the sun was out like normal.

Text.SourceString: What if you climbed to the tippy-top of the island in this storm? I bet the view would be really cool.
Text.LocalizedString: What if you climbed to the tippy-top of the island in this storm? I bet the view would be really cool.

Text.SourceString: Dad says you’d get hit by lightning, though.
Text.LocalizedString: Dad says you’d get hit by lightning, though.

Text.SourceString: A tree keeps hitting the side of our house, and it sounds creepy.//I wish it wasn’t windy anymore.
Text.LocalizedString: A tree keeps hitting the side of our house, and it sounds creepy.//I wish it wasn’t windy anymore.

Text.SourceString: Snow day! <Italic>Yay!</>
Text.LocalizedString: Snow day! <Italic>Yay!</>

Text.SourceString: Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> will have a snowball fight with me later.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> will have a snowball fight with me later.

Text.SourceString: I love watching the snow from in here! It’s so white and fluffy and pretty.
Text.LocalizedString: I love watching the snow from in here! It’s so white and fluffy and pretty.

Text.SourceString: Is the snow still going? It’s gonna be piled up so high tomorrow!
Text.LocalizedString: Is the snow still going? It’s gonna be piled up so high tomorrow!

Text.SourceString: Do you think <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> will close school tomorrow if there’s enough snow outside?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you think <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> will close school tomorrow if there’s enough snow outside?

Text.SourceString: Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> and I can cover the front door in snow so no one can get in.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe <NPCName>Archie</> and I can cover the front door in snow so no one can get in.

Text.SourceString: [<NPCName>Zoe</> is busy with her arts and crafts.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NPCName>Zoe</> is busy with her arts and crafts.]

Text.SourceString: Sometimes <NPCName>Archie</> asks silly questions just to make <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> confused. It’s really funny.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes <NPCName>Archie</> asks silly questions just to make <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> confused. It’s really funny.

Text.SourceString: “<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, what’s a cow?”
Text.LocalizedString: “<NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, what’s a cow?”

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> actually watched <Italic>Prince of Paws</> once!//It’s so cool he watched something my parents made!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</> actually watched <Italic>Prince of Paws</> once!//It’s so cool he watched something my parents made!

Text.SourceString: I hope one day he watches one of my wildlife movies too.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope one day he watches one of my wildlife movies too.

Text.SourceString: Dad? Are there any good cartoons on?
Text.LocalizedString: Dad? Are there any good cartoons on?

Text.SourceString: Oh, you’re not Dad. Do you know if there’s any good cartoons on right now?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, you’re not Dad. Do you know if there’s any good cartoons on right now?

Text.SourceString: Shh! I’m learning about animals.
Text.LocalizedString: Shh! I’m learning about animals.

Text.SourceString: It’s such a nice day outside, right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s such a nice day outside, right?

Text.SourceString: Did you know there’s like ten thousand different kinds of birds out there?
Text.LocalizedString: Did you know there’s like ten thousand different kinds of birds out there?

Text.SourceString: I learned that in a book.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned that in a book.

Text.SourceString: It’s nice to not be in school. I get tired of going there every day.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s nice to not be in school. I get tired of going there every day.

Text.SourceString: Mom and Dad say school ends when you grow up, but I don’t know if I believe them.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom and Dad say school ends when you grow up, but I don’t know if I believe them.

Text.SourceString: Are you gonna tell my mom I’ve been trying to sneak to the recycling center after school?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you gonna tell my mom I’ve been trying to sneak to the recycling center after school?

Text.SourceString: Ugh… I don’t trust you.//You know too much.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… I don’t trust you.//You know too much.

Text.SourceString: I like to go to the library because <NPCName>Millie</> always has a plate of cookies.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to go to the library because <NPCName>Millie</> always has a plate of cookies.

Text.SourceString: If I read a book and talk about it with her afterward, she’ll give me a cookie.
Text.LocalizedString: If I read a book and talk about it with her afterward, she’ll give me a cookie.

Text.SourceString: I read so many books and got so many cookies this week!
Text.LocalizedString: I read so many books and got so many cookies this week!

Text.SourceString: I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.

Text.SourceString: Oh! I saw a cool bird on my walk to school this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! I saw a cool bird on my walk to school this morning.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know what it was. But I bet my dad would know!//He knows everything.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know what it was. But I bet my dad would know!//He knows everything.

Text.SourceString: I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m very careful with animals. Dad said wild animals get scared easily, so we have to show we’re not going to hurt them.

Text.SourceString: I want a pet lizard like <NPCName>Millie’s</>. The ones that live at home always hide from me.
Text.LocalizedString: I want a pet lizard like <NPCName>Millie’s</>. The ones that live at home always hide from me.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Archie</> has the coolest monocular!//He said he found it in the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Archie</> has the coolest monocular!//He said he found it in the forest.

Text.SourceString: So lucky! I wanna go to the forest and find things too!
Text.LocalizedString: So lucky! I wanna go to the forest and find things too!

Text.SourceString: I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait until I’m big and tall like Dad so I can go to the forest by myself.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if I’ll ever grow that big or if I’ll stay small forever.

Text.SourceString: Our house has lizards that go in and out. But Dad said we can’t keep any.
Text.LocalizedString: Our house has lizards that go in and out. But Dad said we can’t keep any.

Text.SourceString: They’re so cute.//I wanna pet them.
Text.LocalizedString: They’re so cute.//I wanna pet them.

Text.SourceString: I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna adopt so many animals when I grow up so that Bonbon can have tons of friends!

Text.SourceString: I wanna travel a lot when I grow up. I can take my bird notebook with me and draw every bird in the whole world.
Text.LocalizedString: I wanna travel a lot when I grow up. I can take my bird notebook with me and draw every bird in the whole world.

Text.SourceString: That’s what my parents do. They travel to see cool birds and other animals.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s what my parents do. They travel to see cool birds and other animals.

Text.SourceString: Yesterday, I scared away a bird my dad and I were watching.//I felt really bad, but he wasn’t mad. He said it happens sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: Yesterday, I scared away a bird my dad and I were watching.//I felt really bad, but he wasn’t mad. He said it happens sometimes.

Text.SourceString: I wish it would happen less.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish it would happen less.

Text.SourceString: My dad found the coolest bird in the forest the other day.//<portrait=normal>He’s so good at finding animals!
Text.LocalizedString: My dad found the coolest bird in the forest the other day.//<portrait=normal>He’s so good at finding animals!

Text.SourceString: That’s why he’s so good at his job.
Text.LocalizedString: That’s why he’s so good at his job.

Text.SourceString: Should I go to the beach today? Or to the park?//<portrait=annoyed> Or maybe <NPCName>Emma’s</> Taco Truck? Ugh, I can’t decide where I want to go!
Text.LocalizedString: Should I go to the beach today? Or to the park?//<portrait=annoyed> Or maybe <NPCName>Emma’s</> Taco Truck? Ugh, I can’t decide where I want to go!

Text.SourceString: I wish there were three <NPCName>Zoes</> so I could go everywhere!
Text.LocalizedString: I wish there were three <NPCName>Zoes</> so I could go everywhere!

Text.SourceString: Making that video was sooooo worth it. Now I know exactly what I’m gonna do when I grow up.
Text.LocalizedString: Making that video was sooooo worth it. Now I know exactly what I’m gonna do when I grow up.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to be a professional bird-watcher!
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to be a professional bird-watcher!

Text.SourceString: This lesson is so boooooring. I don’t wanna learn about the water cycle.//I wanna learn about animals.
Text.LocalizedString: This lesson is so boooooring. I don’t wanna learn about the water cycle.//I wanna learn about animals.

Text.SourceString: I almost showed our bird movie to <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, but I wanna keep it a secret for now.
Text.LocalizedString: I almost showed our bird movie to <NPCName>Mr. Barnes</>, but I wanna keep it a secret for now.

Text.SourceString: I wonder if he saw the bird too.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder if he saw the bird too.

Text.SourceString: Our last test was about animals, so I did super well on it! I even beat <NPCName>Valentina</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Our last test was about animals, so I did super well on it! I even beat <NPCName>Valentina</>.

Text.SourceString: She was all mad and everything. Oops!
Text.LocalizedString: She was all mad and everything. Oops!

Text.SourceString: I haven’t seen that bird since we finished the movie. I wonder if it flew somewhere else.//There’s nothing about it in the library either.
Text.LocalizedString: I haven’t seen that bird since we finished the movie. I wonder if it flew somewhere else.//There’s nothing about it in the library either.

Text.SourceString: I hope I see it again one day.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope I see it again one day.
